<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>From Scars to Purpose: An Interactive Guide</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <!-- Chosen Palette: "Soothing Earth Tones" -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured thematically rather than linearly like the book outline. It uses a top navigation bar for quick access to key areas: 'Home', 'The Wounds' (challenges), 'The Armor' (spiritual tools), 'The Toolkit' (practical exercises), 'Reconnecting' (relationships/purpose), and 'Resources'. This task-oriented design allows a veteran to immediately access the section most relevant to their current need (e.g., jumping directly to anger management exercises in 'The Toolkit'). This is more user-friendly and practical than a linear chapter flow, promoting engagement and providing immediate value. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Since the source is text-based, visualizations are structural and interactive. 'The Wounds' are presented as clickable cards to reveal details, promoting focused exploration. The 'Armor of God' is an interactive HTML/CSS diagram, making the metaphor tangible. The 'Practical Toolkit' is a filterable grid, transforming the book's exercises into an actionable tool. This approach organizes information for quick access and interaction, enhancing understanding and usability. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        }
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap');
        .active-nav {
            color: #A3BFFA;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .nav-link {
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .nav-link:hover {
            color: #A3BFFA;
        }
        .card {
            transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
        }
        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        }
        .toolkit-btn.active {
            background-color: #374151;
            color: #F9FAFB;
        }
        .armor-piece {
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        .armor-piece:hover {
            background-color: #E5E7EB;
        }
        .armor-piece.selected {
            background-color: #D1D5DB;
            border-left-width: 4px;
            border-color: #6B7280;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-[#FDF8F0] text-[#3A3A3A]">

    <header class="bg-[#4A5568] text-white p-4 sticky top-0 z-50 shadow-md">
        <div class="container mx-auto flex justify-between items-center">
            <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">From Scars to Purpose</h1>
            <nav class="hidden md:flex space-x-6">
                <a href="#home" class="nav-link active-nav">Home</a>
                <a href="#wounds" class="nav-link">The Wounds</a>
                <a href="#armor" class="nav-link">The Armor</a>
                <a href="#toolkit" class="nav-link">The Toolkit</a>
                <a href="#reconnecting" class="nav-link">Reconnecting</a>
                <a href="#resources" class="nav-link">Resources</a>
            </nav>
            <button id="mobile-menu-button" class="md:hidden focus:outline-none">
                <span class="block w-6 h-0.5 bg-white mb-1"></span>
                <span class="block w-6 h-0.5 bg-white mb-1"></span>
                <span class="block w-6 h-0.5 bg-white"></span>
            </button>
        </div>
        <div id="mobile-menu" class="hidden md:hidden mt-4">
            <a href="#home" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">Home</a>
            <a href="#wounds" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">The Wounds</a>
            <a href="#armor" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">The Armor</a>
            <a href="#toolkit" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">The Toolkit</a>
            <a href="#reconnecting" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">Reconnecting</a>
            <a href="#resources" class="block py-2 px-4 text-sm hover:bg-[#6B7280]">Resources</a>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container mx-auto p-4 md:p-8">

        <section id="home" class="text-center py-16 md:py-24">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-4">Welcome Home, Warrior.</h2>
            <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-[#4A5568] mb-6">Coming home isn't just a change of address; it's a transition from one battlefield to another. This guide is a shared space for veterans, offering a path to healing that combines the timeless wisdom of scripture with practical, actionable steps.</p>
            <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-[#4A5568] font-semibold italic">"The Lord is near to the brokenhearted and saves the crushed in spirit." (Psalm 34:18)</p>
        </section>

        <section id="wounds" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-16">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#2D3748]">Understanding the Wounds</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[#4A5568] max-w-2xl mx-auto">The first step to healing is to define the enemy. These are not personal failures; they are legitimate wounds of the soul. Click on a topic below to learn more about its nature and the unique challenges veterans face.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="wounds-grid" class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="armor" class="py-16 md:py-24 mb-16">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#2D3748]">Equipping for a New Battle</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[#4A5568] max-w-2xl mx-auto">In Ephesians 6, we're given a spiritual uniform for this new battle. Each piece has a specific purpose in protecting your mind and spirit. Click on each piece of the Armor of God to understand its function.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <div id="armor-list" class="w-full md:w-1/3 border-r border-gray-200 pr-4">
                </div>
                <div id="armor-display" class="w-full md:w-2/3 pl-4">
                    <div id="armor-content-placeholder" class="text-center text-gray-500 flex items-center justify-center h-full">
                        <p>Select a piece of armor to see its description.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="toolkit" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-16">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#2D3748]">The Practical Toolkit</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[#4A5568] max-w-2xl mx-auto">Faith is active. This toolkit provides practical, actionable exercises to help you navigate the challenges of healing. Filter the exercises by the area you need to focus on today.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="toolkit-filters" class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2 mb-8">
            </div>
            <div id="toolkit-grid" class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="reconnecting" class="py-16 md:py-24 mb-16">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#2D3748]">Reconnecting & Finding Purpose</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[#4A5568] max-w-2xl mx-auto">Healing involves rebuilding connections with family, community, and your own sense of mission. Explore the principles for strengthening your relationships and finding your new purpose beyond the uniform.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-4">Coming Home to Family</h3>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] mb-4">An invisible emotional gap can form between a veteran and their loved ones. Closing it requires intentional communication, patience, and love. It's about learning to speak a shared language again.</p>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] italic font-semibold">"Love is patient and kind... it bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things." (1 Corinthians 13:4-7)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-4">Finding Your New Mission</h3>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] mb-4">Leaving the service can feel like losing your purpose. But your work, no matter what it is, can be a form of worship and service. Your new mission is to use your unique skills to serve God and others where you are.</p>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] italic font-semibold">"And my God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus." (Philippians 4:19)</p>
                </div>
                 <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-4">Finding Your Tribe</h3>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] mb-4">You never fight alone in the military, and you shouldn't fight alone now. Finding a new, healthy community in a church or support group is critical. Your struggles are not a curse; they are a testimony that can help others.</p>
                    <p class="text-[#4A5568] italic font-semibold">"Let us not grow weary of doing good, for in due season we will reap, if we do not give up." (Galatians 6:9)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="resources" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-[#4A5568] text-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Resources & Next Steps</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-lg opacity-90 max-w-2xl mx-auto">You are not alone. Here are some immediate resources and reminders to support your journey of healing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
                <div class="bg-[#6B7280] p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Emergency Toolkit</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-2">
                        <li><strong>In a Crisis:</strong> Call or text 988, then press 1.</li>
                        <li><strong>Anxiety Attack:</strong> Use the 5-4-3-2-1 grounding method.</li>
                        <li><strong>Anger Flare-up:</strong> Use the "Pause and Pray" method.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#6B7280] p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Recommended Connections</h3>
                     <ul class="space-y-2">
                        <li><strong>Veterans-Specific:</strong> The Wounded Warrior Project, local VFW chapters.</li>
                        <li><strong>Faith-Based:</strong> Celebrate Recovery, local church support groups.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#6B7280] p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">The Power of Physical Wellness</h3>
                    <p>Your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit. Exercise, good nutrition, and adequate sleep are crucial components of emotional and spiritual healing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="text-center py-6 bg-[#2D3748] text-gray-300">
        <p>&copy; 2025 From Scars to Purpose. A guide for healing.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
            const woundsData = [
                { title: "Anger", content: "Anger can feel like a rush of power, but it’s an unseen grenade. It's often a secondary emotion, a smokescreen for deeper trauma, fear, or a sense of injustice. The key is to differentiate righteous anger from destructive rage.", scripture: "Psalm 147:3" },
                { title: "Depression & Anxiety", content: "These are not just 'bad feelings.' They are a dense fog of war that can obscure your mission and isolate you. They require both spiritual and practical care to navigate.", scripture: "Philippians 4:6-7" },
                { title: "PTSD", content: "PTSD creates echoes of the past that bleed into the present through triggers and flashbacks. Healing involves rebuilding your foundation in the present moment and reclaiming your story.", scripture: "2 Timothy 1:7" },
                { title: "Addiction", content: "Addiction is often a search for comfort or escape from pain. It's a false comforter. True freedom is found not in a quick fix, but in a new allegiance to Christ, the ultimate source of freedom.", scripture: "John 8:36" },
                { title: "Grief & Loss", content: "Grief for veterans isn't just about funerals. It's the loss of comrades, identity, and a way of life. Healing isn't about forgetting, but re-contextualizing memories to honor the past without being defined by it.", scripture: "Psalm 23:1, 3" }
            ];

            const armorData = [
                { piece: "The Belt of Truth", description: "The foundation of your armor. The enemy thrives on lies. We must confront these lies with the unshakeable truth of God’s Word." },
                { piece: "The Breastplate of Righteousness", description: "Your identity is no longer in your past. Your righteousness is found only in Christ. This protects your heart from shame and condemnation." },
                { piece: "The Shoes of the Gospel of Peace", description: "You are no longer on a mission of conflict, but of peace. These shoes give you stability and readiness to move forward." },
                { piece: "The Shield of Faith", description: "Your defense against every fiery dart of the enemy. It is your confidence in God's promises that deflects doubts, anxieties, and fears." },
                { piece: "The Helmet of Salvation", description: "This protects your mind, your central command. It reminds you of your eternal security in Christ, no matter what you face." },
                { piece: "The Sword of the Spirit", description: "The only offensive weapon in your arsenal, this is the Word of God. The scriptures are your weapon for spiritual combat." }
            ];

            const toolkitData = [
                { title: "Pause and Pray Method", category: "Anger", description: "When anger flares, physically stop, take a deep breath, and pray for guidance before reacting. This interrupts the cycle of destructive rage." },
                { title: "Gratitude in the Trenches", category: "Depression & Anxiety", description: "A simple journaling exercise to document three small things you are grateful for each day, even on the darkest days." },
                { title: "Grounding with 5-4-3-2-1", category: "PTSD", description: "Use your senses to anchor yourself in the present. Name 5 things you see, 4 you feel, 3 you hear, 2 you smell, and 1 you taste." },
                { title: "Replacing Habits", category: "Addiction", description: "Identify a trigger for a negative habit and replace the action with a positive, faith-based one, like listening to a worship song." },
                { title: "A 'Goodbye' Letter", category: "Grief & Loss", description: "A reflective writing exercise to process unspoken feelings of grief by writing a letter to what was lost. This is a sacred act of letting go." },
                { title: "Listen and Learn Method", category: "Family", description: "A structured communication exercise for veterans and families to practice active listening without judgment, taking turns to speak and listen." }
            ];

            const woundsGrid = document.getElementById('wounds-grid');
            woundsData.forEach(item => {
                const card = document.createElement('div');
                card.className = 'card bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md cursor-pointer';
                card.innerHTML = `<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-2">${item.title}</h3><p class="text-gray-600">${item.content}</p>`;
                card.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    const existingDetail = card.querySelector('.detail');
                    if (existingDetail) {
                        existingDetail.remove();
                    } else {
                        const detail = document.createElement('div');
                        detail.className = 'detail mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded';
                        detail.innerHTML = `<p class="font-semibold italic">"He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds." (Psalm 147:3)</p>`;
                        card.appendChild(detail);
                    }
                });
                woundsGrid.appendChild(card);
            });

            const armorList = document.getElementById('armor-list');
            const armorDisplay = document.getElementById('armor-display');
            const armorPlaceholder = document.getElementById('armor-content-placeholder');
            armorData.forEach((item, index) => {
                const piece = document.createElement('div');
                piece.className = 'armor-piece p-4 rounded';
                piece.textContent = item.piece;
                piece.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    armorPlaceholder.style.display = 'none';
                    armorDisplay.innerHTML = `<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mb-4">${item.piece}</h3><p class="text-lg text-[#4A5568]">${item.description}</p>`;
                    
                    document.querySelectorAll('.armor-piece').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('selected'));
                    piece.classList.add('selected');
                });
                armorList.appendChild(piece);
            });

            const toolkitFilters = document.getElementById('toolkit-filters');
            const toolkitGrid = document.getElementById('toolkit-grid');
            const categories = ['All', ...new Set(toolkitData.map(item => item.category))];
            
            categories.forEach(category => {
                const button = document.createElement('button');
                button.className = 'toolkit-btn px-4 py-2 bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold transition';
                button.textContent = category;
                if (category === 'All') button.classList.add('active');
                button.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    document.querySelectorAll('.toolkit-btn').forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
                    button.classList.add('active');
                    filterToolkit(category);
                });
                toolkitFilters.appendChild(button);
            });

            const filterToolkit = (category) => {
                toolkitGrid.innerHTML = '';
                const filteredData = category === 'All' ? toolkitData : toolkitData.filter(item => item.category === category);
                filteredData.forEach(item => {
                    const card = document.createElement('div');
                    card.className = 'card bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md';
                    card.innerHTML = `
                        <span class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-semibold mr-2 px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full">${item.category}</span>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#2D3748] mt-3 mb-2">${item.title}</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600">${item.description}</p>
                    `;
                    toolkitGrid.appendChild(card);
                });
            };
            filterToolkit('All');

            const mobileMenuButton = document.getElementById('mobile-menu-button');
            const mobileMenu = document.getElementById('mobile-menu');
            mobileMenuButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
                mobileMenu.classList.toggle('hidden');
            });
            
            document.querySelectorAll('#mobile-menu a').forEach(link => {
                link.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    mobileMenu.classList.add('hidden');
                });
            });

            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('nav a');
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    if (pageYOffset >= sectionTop - 60) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });
                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active-nav');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').includes(current)) {
                        link.classList.add('active-nav');
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
